{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "14", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "03", "M": "06", "S": "03"}}, "news": [{"title": "Builders pledge full compliance as GRAP stage-III curbs take effect across NCR", "para": "Delhi-NCR's air quality has entered the 'severe' category, prompting the Commission for Air Quality Management to invoke Stage-III of the Graded Response Action Plan. This triggers immediate restrictions on various construction and demolition activities across the region. Real estate developers have pledged full compliance, emphasizing environmental responsibility and dust-mitigation measures.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ncr-construction-activities-restricted-as-air-quality-deteriorates/125314808?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-30578/125314808.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Delhi civic body to install CCTV cameras at 524 spots to tackle construction dumping", "para": "The Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) is installing CCTV cameras at 524 locations to combat illegal dumping of construction and demolition waste. This initiative aims to identify and penalize habitual offenders, complementing existing designated dumping sites and processing plants. The city generates substantial C&D waste daily, with efforts underway to increase processing capacity and improve waste management infrastructure.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/mcd-to-combat-construction-waste-524-cctv-cameras-to-be-installed-in-delhi/125293965?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-93654/125293965.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Sub-registrar, realtor arrested in land-grab case in Bengaluru", "para": "Bengaluru CCB sleuths have arrested a sub-registrar and a realtor-cum-middleman in a land-grab case involving forged documents and the sale of multiple residential sites without the landowner's knowledge. The August 2022 case, initially filed at Parappana Agrahara police station, has led to the arrest of approximately 100 suspects so far.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/sub-registrar-and-realtor-arrested-in-major-bengaluru-land-grabbing-scandal/125293915?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32062/125293915.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}